main event: A UFO report from Project Blue Book dated 9 July 1950 describes an unidentified flying object observation in Peck, Montana.
interesting points: The report involves a pilot and crew with 26 and 28 years of experience, respectively., The UFO was reported to be circular in shape., The sighting was observed while flying at approximately 13,000 feet., The document was heavily redacted, obscuring much of the text., The date of the report suggests a historical context within the early years of the UFO investigation.
sighted object: unidentified flying object, circular in shape
witness description: Pilot aged 26 and crew aged 28, both have extensive flight experience.
